  "prompt": "Is Masters in Public Health course included in SOL?",
  "response": "The UK's Shortage Occupation List (SOL) specifies which occupations are considered to be in short supply within the country. Whether a specific course like a Master's in Public Health is included in the SOL depends on the specific careers and job roles associated with the degree.\n\nPublic health professionals may fall under various categories in the SOL, such as medical practitioners, health professionals, or other related roles. The SOL is regularly updated, so it is important to check the latest information on the UK Home Office website or consult an immigration advisor for the most current details.\n\nAs of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, public health roles like epidemiologists, biostatisticians, and health service managers may be in shortage, but you should verify the exact occupations and eligibility criteria from official sources.",
